msgid "Advanced vector math"
msgstr "Ardmatamaitic veicteora"

msgid "Planes"
msgstr "Plánaí"

msgid ""
"The dot product has another interesting property with unit vectors. Imagine "
"that perpendicular to that vector (and through the origin) passes a plane. "
"Planes divide the entire space into positive (over the plane) and negative "
"(under the plane), and (contrary to popular belief) you can also use their "
"math in 2D:"
msgstr ""
"Tá maoin spéisiúil eile ag an táirge ponc le veicteoirí aonaid. Samhlaigh go "
"dtéann eitleán ingearach leis an veicteoir sin (agus tríd an mbunús). "
"Roinneann plánaí an spás iomlán ina dhearfach (thar an eitleán) agus "
"diúltach (faoin eitleán), agus (contrártha leis an gcreideamh coitianta) is "
"féidir leat a gcuid matamaitic a úsáid i 2D freisin:"

msgid ""
"Unit vectors that are perpendicular to a surface (so, they describe the "
"orientation of the surface) are called **unit normal vectors**. Though, "
"usually they are just abbreviated as *normals*. Normals appear in planes, 3D "
"geometry (to determine where each face or vertex is siding), etc. A "
"**normal** *is* a **unit vector**, but it's called *normal* because of its "
"usage. (Just like we call (0,0) the Origin!)."
msgstr ""
"Tugtar gnáthfhreagairí aonaid** ar veicteoirí aonaid atá ingearach le "
"dromchla (mar sin, déanann siad cur síos ar threoshuíomh an dromchla). Mar "
"sin féin, de ghnáth ní ghiorraítear iad mar ghnáth*. Tá gnáthchúlacha le "
"feiceáil i bplánaí, geoiméadracht 3D (chun a chinneadh cá bhfuil gach "
"aghaidh nó beart ag taobhanna), srl. Is gnáth** ** veigtheoir aonaid**, ach "
"tugtar uir* gnáth* mar gheall ar a úsáid. (Díreach mar a thugaimid ar (0,0) "
"an Bunús!)."

msgid "Distance to plane"
msgstr "Fad go dtí an eitleán"

msgid ""
"Now that it's clear what a plane is, let's go back to the dot product. The "
"dot product between a **unit vector** and any **point in space** (yes, this "
"time we do dot product between vector and position), returns the **distance "
"from the point to the plane**:"
msgstr ""
"Anois go bhfuil sé soiléir cad é eitleán, déanaimis ar ais chuig an táirge "
"ponc. Tugann an táirge ponc idir **vector aonaid** agus aon **pointe sa "
"spás** (sea, an uair seo déanaimid ponc táirge idir veicteoir agus suíomh), "
"an **achar ón bpointe go dtí an plán** ar ais:"

msgid ""
"But not just the absolute distance, if the point is in the negative half "
"space the distance will be negative, too:"
msgstr ""
"Ach ní amháin an fad iomlán, má tá an pointe sa leathspás diúltach beidh an "
"fad diúltach freisin:"

msgid "This allows us to tell which side of the plane a point is."
msgstr "Ligeann sé seo dúinn a rá cén taobh den eitleán atá pointe."

msgid "Away from the origin"
msgstr "Ar shiúl ón mbunús"

msgid ""
"I know what you are thinking! So far this is nice, but *real* planes are "
"everywhere in space, not only passing through the origin. You want real "
"*plane* action and you want it *now*."
msgstr ""
"Tá a fhios agam cad atá tú ag smaoineamh! Go dtí seo tá sé seo deas, ach tá "
"plánaí* fíor* i ngach áit sa spás, ní amháin go dtéann tríd an mbunús. "
"Teastaíonn fíor-ghníomhaíocht phlean* uait agus teastaíonn uait* anois*."

msgid ""
"Remember that planes not only split space in two, but they also have "
"*polarity*. This means that it is possible to have perfectly overlapping "
"planes, but their negative and positive half-spaces are swapped."
msgstr ""
"Cuimhnigh nach amháin go roinntear eitleáin spás ina dhá cheann, ach tá * "
"polaracht* acu freisin. Ciallaíonn sé seo gur féidir eitleanna forluí go "
"foirfe a bheith agat, ach déantar a leath-spásanna diúltacha agus dearfacha "
"a mhalartú."

