msgid ""
"So, remember, the plane's main practical use is that we can calculate the "
"distance to it. So, when is it useful to calculate the distance from a point "
"to a plane? Let's see some examples."
msgstr ""
"Mar sin, cuimhnigh, is é príomh-úsáid phraiticiúil an eitleáin gur féidir "
"linn an fad uaidh a ríomh. Mar sin, cathain a bhíonn sé úsáideach an fad ó "
"phointe go eitleán a ríomh? Feicfimid roinnt samplaí."

msgid "Constructing a plane in 2D"
msgstr "Ag tógáil eitleán i 2D"

msgid ""
"Planes clearly don't come out of nowhere, so they must be built. "
"Constructing them in 2D is easy, this can be done from either a normal (unit "
"vector) and a point, or from two points in space."
msgstr ""
"Is léir nach dtagann eitleáin as áit ar bith, mar sin caithfear iad a "
"thógáil. Tá sé furasta iad a thógáil i 2D, is féidir é seo a dhéanamh ó "
"ghnáth (veicteoir aonaid) agus pointe, nó ó dhá phointe sa spás."

msgid ""
"In the case of a normal and a point, most of the work is done, as the normal "
"is already computed, so calculate D from the dot product of the normal and "
"the point."
msgstr ""
"I gcás gnáthphointe agus pointe, déantar an chuid is mó den obair, mar go "
"bhfuil an gnáth ríomhaithe cheana féin, mar sin ríomh D ó tháirge ponc an "
"ghnáth agus an phointe."

msgid ""
"The rest is the same as the previous example. Either point_a or point_b will "
"work, as they are in the same plane:"
msgstr ""
"Tá an chuid eile mar an gcéanna leis an sampla roimhe seo. Oibreoidh point_a "
"nó point_b, mar go bhfuil siad san eitleán céanna:"

msgid ""
"Doing the same in 3D is a little more complex and is explained further down."
msgstr ""
"Tá an rud céanna a dhéanamh i 3D rud beagán níos casta agus mínítear níos "
"faide síos."

msgid "Some examples of planes"
msgstr "Roinnt samplaí d'eitleáin"

msgid ""
"Here is an example of what planes are useful for. Imagine you have a `convex "
"<https://www.mathsisfun.com/definitions/convex.html>`__ polygon. For "
"example, a rectangle, a trapezoid, a triangle, or just any polygon where no "
"faces bend inwards."
msgstr ""
"Seo sampla de na rudaí a bhfuil eitleáin úsáideach dóibh. Samhlaigh go "
"bhfuil polagán `dronnach <https://www.mathsisfun.com/definitions/convex."
"html>`__ agat. Mar shampla, dronuilleog, trapezoid, triantán, nó díreach "
"polagán ar bith nach lúbann aghaidheanna isteach."

msgid ""
"For every segment of the polygon, we compute the plane that passes by that "
"segment. Once we have the list of planes, we can do neat things, for example "
"checking if a point is inside the polygon."
msgstr ""
"I gcás gach deighleog den pholygón, ríomhaímid an eitleán a théann tríd an "
"deighleog sin. Nuair a bheidh liosta na n-eitleáin againn, is féidir linn "
"rudaí néata a dhéanamh, mar shampla seiceáil an bhfuil pointe taobh istigh "
"den pholygón."

msgid ""
"We go through all planes, if we can find a plane where the distance to the "
"point is positive, then the point is outside the polygon. If we can't, then "
"the point is inside."
msgstr ""
"Téimid trí gach eitleán, más féidir linn eitleán a fháil ina bhfuil an fad "
"go dtí an pointe dearfach, ansin tá an pointe lasmuigh den pholygón. Mura "
"féidir linn, ansin tá an pointe taobh istigh."

msgid "Code should be something like this:"
msgstr "Ba chóir go mbeadh an cód mar seo:"

msgid ""
"Pretty cool, huh? But this gets much better! With a little more effort, "
"similar logic will let us know when two convex polygons are overlapping too. "
"This is called the Separating Axis Theorem (or SAT) and most physics engines "
"use this to detect collision."
msgstr ""
"Fhionnuar go leor, huh? Ach éiríonn sé seo i bhfad níos fearr! Le beagán "
"níos mó iarrachta, cuirfidh loighic den chineál céanna in iúl dúinn nuair a "
"bhíonn dhá pholagán doimhe forluí freisin. Tugtar Teoirim Ais Scartha (nó "
"SAT) air seo agus úsáideann mórchuid na n-innill fhisice é seo chun "
"imbhualadh a bhrath."

msgid ""
"With a point, just checking if a plane returns a positive distance is enough "
"to tell if the point is outside. With another polygon, we must find a plane "
"where *all* *the* *other* *polygon* *points* return a positive distance to "
"it. This check is performed with the planes of A against the points of B, "
"and then with the planes of B against the points of A:"
msgstr ""
"Le pointe, is leor ach seiceáil an bhfilleann eitleán achar dearfach chun a "
"rá an bhfuil an pointe lasmuigh. Le polagón eile, ní mór dúinn eitleán a "
"aimsiú ina bhfill* uach* ** eala* *polagón* * pointí eile* achar dearfach a "
"thabhairt air. Déantar an seiceáil seo le plánaí A i gcoinne pointí B, agus "
"ansin le plánaí B i gcoinne pointí A:"

msgid ""
"As you can see, planes are quite useful, and this is the tip of the iceberg. "
"You might be wondering what happens with non convex polygons. This is "
"usually just handled by splitting the concave polygon into smaller convex "
"polygons, or using a technique such as BSP (which is not used much nowadays)."
msgstr ""
"Mar a fheiceann tú, tá eitleáin úsáideach go leor, agus is é seo barr an "
"oighir. B'fhéidir go mbeadh tú ag smaoineamh cad a tharlaíonn le polagóin "
"neamh-doirb De ghnáth ní dhéantar é seo a láimhseáil ach tríd an bpolagán "
"concave a roinnt ina pholagóin doimhneach níos lú, nó teicníc mar BSP a "
"úsáid (nach n-úsáidtear go mór sa lá atá inniu ann)."

msgid "Collision detection in 3D"
msgstr "Braite imbhualadh i 3D"

msgid ""
"This is another bonus bit, a reward for being patient and keeping up with "
"this long tutorial. Here is another piece of wisdom. This might not be "
"something with a direct use case (Godot already does collision detection "
"pretty well) but it's used by almost all physics engines and collision "
"detection libraries :)"
msgstr ""
"Is giotán bónais eile é seo, luach saothair as a bheith foighneach agus "
"coinneáil suas leis an rang teagaisc fhada seo. Seo píosa eagna eile. "
"B'fhéidir nach rud é seo le cás úsáide díreach (déanann Godot braite "
"imbhualadh go maith cheana féin) ach úsáideann beagnach gach inneall fisice "
"agus leabharlanna braite imbhuailte é:)"

msgid ""
"Remember that converting a convex shape in 2D to an array of 2D planes was "
"useful for collision detection? You could detect if a point was inside any "
"convex shape, or if two 2D convex shapes were overlapping."
msgstr ""
"Cuimhnigh go raibh cruth doimhneach a thiontú i 2D go sraith eitleáin 2D "
"úsáideach chun imbhualadh a bhrath? D'fhéadfá a bhrath an raibh pointe taobh "
"istigh d'aon chruth doimhneach, nó an raibh dhá chruth doimhneach 2D ag "
"forluí."

msgid ""
"Well, this works in 3D too, if two 3D polyhedral shapes are colliding, you "
"won't be able to find a separating plane. If a separating plane is found, "
"then the shapes are definitely not colliding."
msgstr ""
"Bhuel, oibríonn sé seo i 3D freisin, má tá dhá chruth polyhedral 3D ag "
"imbhualadh, ní bheidh tú in ann eitleán scartha a fháil. Má aimsítear "
"eitleán scartha, ansin is cinnte nach bhfuil na cruthanna ag imbhualadh."

msgid ""
"To refresh a bit a separating plane means that all vertices of polygon A are "
"in one side of the plane, and all vertices of polygon B are in the other "
"side. This plane is always one of the face-planes of either polygon A or "
"polygon B."
msgstr ""
"Chun beagán a athnuachan ciallaíonn eitleán scartha go bhfuil gach beart de "
"pholagún A i dtaobh amháin den eitleán, agus go bhfuil gach beart de "
"pholagún B sa taobh eile. Tá an t-eitleán seo i gcónaí ar cheann de na "
"plánaí aghaidhe de pholygón A nó polagún B."

msgid ""
"In 3D though, there is a problem to this approach, because it is possible "
"that, in some cases a separating plane can't be found. This is an example of "
"such situation:"
msgstr ""
"I 3D áfach, tá fadhb leis an gcur chuige seo, mar is féidir, i gcásanna "
"áirithe, eitleán scartha a fháil. Seo sampla den chás den sórt sin:"

msgid ""
"To avoid it, some extra planes need to be tested as separators, these planes "
"are the cross product between the edges of polygon A and the edges of "
"polygon B"
msgstr ""
"Chun é a sheachaint, caithfear roinnt eitleáin bhreise a thástáil mar "
"scarthóirí, is iad na plánaí seo an trastháirge idir imill polagún A agus "
"imill polagún B"

